  <prompt>
    Add prominent **RETIRED** banners to two R1-legacy architecture documents per FR-27 items #10 and #11:

    (a) `docs/architecture/email-to-document-architecture.md`
    (b) `docs/architecture/email-to-document-automation.md`

    Both docs describe R1's `/api/v1/emails/*` Power Apps Email-activity subsystem — confirmed dead in production usage per the driver assessment (out of scope for R3 per spec). Banner format: bold notice at top with link to ADR-033 + the driver assessment + a "do not implement against this doc" warning.

    The docs are NOT deleted (preserves history); they are clearly marked as no-longer-canonical.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke documentation maintainer applying retirement banners. Familiar with the precedent for retirement banners (see `docs/architecture/LEGALWORKSPACE-RETIREMENT.md` for prior retirement language).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Both legacy docs have visible RETIRED banners at the top, with links to ADR-033 (canonical replacement) + the driver assessment + a clear warning that no new code should be written against these docs.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec Out of Scope: "`/api/v1/emails/*` Power Apps Email-activity subsystem (dead in production usage per assessment §3.3)". The two architecture docs describing this subsystem are R1 legacy and should not guide new work.

      Backlog item #12 (filed in Wave 0 task 006) is "Investigate retirement of `/api/v1/emails/*`" — actual code retirement is OUT OF SCOPE for R3 (separate project). This task only handles the documentation-side marking.
    </background>
