  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `docs/architecture/LEGALWORKSPACE-RETIREMENT.md` (and any other retirement-marked doc found via grep) to extract the standard banner template.</step>
    <step order="2">Read both target docs to find their top-of-file structure and decide on banner placement (typically immediately after the H1 title).</step>
    <step order="3">Author the banner template (one banner used for both docs):
      ```
      > **⚠ RETIRED — 2026-06-05**
      >
      > This document describes the R1 Power Apps Email-activity subsystem (`/api/v1/emails/*`), which is **dead in production usage** per the [Communication Architecture Assessment 2026-06-05](../assessments/communication-architecture-assessment-2026-06-05.md).
      >
      > The canonical email architecture is **[ADR-033 Communication Architecture](../../.claude/adr/ADR-033-communication-architecture.md)** — `<EmailComposer />` engine + 3 wrappers + Code Page + typed wrapper.
      >
      > **DO NOT implement new code against this document.** Backlog item #12 covers eventual code retirement of `/api/v1/emails/*`.
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="4">Apply banner to `docs/architecture/email-to-document-architecture.md` (top of file, immediately after H1).</step>
    <step order="5">Apply banner to `docs/architecture/email-to-document-automation.md` (top of file, immediately after H1).</step>
